{# Mid-session user adjustment, wrapped as a follow-up prompt. #}
{# Required context: user_text, current_stage (str, may be "starting"),
   stages_summary (str), files_summary (str), pivot_immediately (bool),
   coordinator_followup (str, optional -- if the coordinator already
   rendered a precise prompt, it goes here verbatim). #}
{% if coordinator_followup %}
{{ coordinator_followup | trim }}
{% else %}
# User adjustment

The user has issued a change of direction mid-task.

What's been done so far: {{ stages_summary | default("(nothing yet)", true) }}.
Files touched: {{ files_summary | default("(none)", true) }}.

User's adjustment: "{{ user_text | trim }}"

{% if pivot_immediately %}
Apply this adjustment immediately. Stop the current line of work, pivot
to the new direction, and continue from there. Make the change consistent
with what's already been built when possible; flag conflicts via
`mcp__kenning_coding__request_clarification` if you'd have to redo
substantial work.
{% else %}
Finish the current step you're on, then apply the adjustment. The new
direction takes precedence for everything after the current step.
{% endif %}

Same testing + reporting protocol applies.
{% endif %}
